data.name: Flytac 120 - 90W
data.description: Flytac 120 - 90W is a granular, water-white, modified gum rosin polyols esters made from specially refined gum rosin using a series of advanced processes of partial hydrogenation, esterification, and stabilization. They are a new generation of natural tackifier resins that exhibit good aging resistance, and excellent compatibility. Also capable of raising the initial and persistent viscosity of pressure-sensitive adhesive in a simultaneous way, the excellent heat stability increases by less than 1 degree of Gardner Color within consecutive 8 hours at 180°C.

data.name: Dragonox® PDP
data.description: Dragonox® PDP is a liquid-type antioxidant with good color and heat stability. This product is widely used in polyvinyl chloride (PVC), acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS), polyurethanes (PU), polycarbonates (PC), and coatings.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 3039
data.description: Dragonsorb® 3039 is a liquid UV absorber with a stable morphology. It has good compatibility with all common plasticizers. This product is especially suitable for the stabilizers of PVC-P and PVC plastisol. It can also be used in polyurethane (PUR), polyester, polymethacrylate (PMMA), and other materials to improve the weatherability of the materials under UV conditions.

data.name: Flytac 103 - E

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Glycerol ester of disproportionated rosin, Glycerol ester of wood rosin

data.description:
Flytac 103 - E is a slightly yellow, transparent solid made from gum rosin through esterification with glycerol. This product has a high viscosity, low VOC, excellent heat and aging stability, excellent polymer compatibility, etc.
Typical Uses

EVA, SBS, SIS, and other hot melt adhesives due to their stability and excellent polymer compatibility.
It can also be used in construction adhesives, rubber compounding, sealants, coatings, and other applications.

data.name: Flyadd® AY1
data.description: Flyadd® AY1 is a color stabilizer and anti-yellowing agent. It is used as a polymer additive for polyurethane and is a highly effective additive for many kinds of dispersed polymer systems. This product has the potential to improve color and heat stability in processing and end applications.

data.name: Dragonox® 1135
data.description: Dragonox® 1135 is an excellent antioxidant that may be used in a variety of polymers. Because of its low volatility and excellent compatibility, it is particularly well suited for use in forced air cooling processes for PU. This product is used in the stabilization of PV flexible slabstock foams to prevent the formation of peroxides in the polyol during storage and transport and to further protect against scorching during foaming. It also helps prevent fogging in automotive applications, and the low volatility of this product makes it a perfect fit where meat liquids, emulsions, suspensions, solutions, or melts are an integral part of polymer manufacturing and processing. This product has the convenience of a pumpable liquid that can be added before, during, or after polymerization.

data.name: Dragonox® 1315
data.description: Dragonox® 1315 is a low-viscosity liquid-type antioxidant. Due to its alkyl chain, this product has a broad compatibility range and is soluble in various substances. It is an excellent antioxidant for polymers (such as PVC, ABS, etc.), lubricating oil, and polyurethane foam.

data.text_description: We deal with benzotriazole, benzophenone, HALS types of UV absorbers and Light Stabilizers.
data.seo_title: Dragonsorb - Guangzhou Flying Dragon Chemical Ltd. - Benzophenone
data.seo_description: We deal with benzotriazole, benzophenone, HALS types of UV absorbers and Light Stabilizers.

filters.filter_name: Butanedioc acid, dimethylester, polymer with 4-hydroxy-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-1-piperidine ethanol

data.name: Dragonsorb® PR-25
data.description: Dragonsorb® PR-25 is a highly effective UV absorber. This white crystalline powdered provides excellent UV stability to ABS, PA, PET, PC, PS, and PVC.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 384-2

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Benzenepropanoic acid, 3-(2H-benzotriazol-2-yl)-5-(1,1-dimethylethyl)-4-hydroxy-, C 7-9-branched and linear alkyl esters

data.description: Dragonsorb® 384-2 has good thermal stability and compatibility with various polymers. This product can be used in automotive coatings and general industrial coatings, such as coil coatings and wood coatings. It can be used in combination with hindered amine light stabilizers, such as Dragonsorb® 292 or Dragonsorb® 123. The synergistic effect of these additives can provide better inhibition of yellowing, cracking, blistering, peeling, and extinction of coatings.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 3853PP5
data.description:
Dragonsorb® 3853PP5 is a UV absorber that is mainly used for the following applications:

Polyethylene (PE): Flat wire, injection molding, and roll molding products.
Polypropylene (PP): Flat wire, film, injection molding products, TPO, polyolefin alloy, hips, ABS, and ASA.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 3853S
data.description: Dragonsorb® 3853S functions as a UV absorber. This white or off-white granulated product finds application in the manufacture of PE tapes, injection moldings, sheets, metallocene, PP films, tapes, fibers, TPO polyacetals, ASA, ABS, and HIPS.

data.name: Dragonsorb® B75
data.description: Dragonsorb® B75 is a mixture of an antioxidant, a benzotriazole-type ultraviolet absorber, and a hindered amine light stabilizer. This product is suitable for rim polyurethane and TPU, as well as sealants and adhesives. It has good applications in waterproof canvas, floors, and polyurethane coating in synthetic leather.

data.name: Dragonsorb® BP6

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 2-(2-Hydroxy-4-methoxybenzoyl)-5-methoxyphenol, 2,2′-Dihydroxy-4,4′-dimethoxybenzophenone, 4,4′-Dimethoxy-2,2′-dihydroxybenzophenone, NSC 40149, Casein Potassium Complex, Potassium Casein Complex

data.description: Dragonsorb® BP6 is a kind of water-soluble, neutral, broad-spectrum benzophenone ultraviolet absorber. It has a high absorption efficiency, is non-toxic, has no teratogenic side effects, and has good light and thermal stability. At present, it is the most commonly used light stabilizer, which can strongly and selectively absorb high-energy ultraviolet light and conduct energy conversion in the form of thermal energy. This substance is mainly used in water-soluble chemical sunscreens, sunscreens, and emulsions. It can improve the color durability of dyed textiles, prevent wool textiles from yellowing and synthetic fiber fabrics from fading, and can also be used in hair gel, mousse, and other hair products to prevent hair damage such as graying of hair caused by ultraviolet radiation.

data.name: Dragonsorb® P
data.description: Dragonsorb® P is an ultraviolet absorption agent with a maximum absorption wavelength of 270 - 380nm. It is available for polyester, epoxy, cellulose acetate, PVC, polystyrene, plexiglass, polyacrylonitrile resin, etc. The general consumption of this product is 0.1 - 0.5% for thin matter and 0.05 - 0.2% for thick matter.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 1
data.description: Dragonsorb® 1 is a highly efficient liquid-type UV absorber with an effective UV absorption range of 240 - 350nm. It has excellent light stability for polyurethane products like flexible foam, rigid foam, elastomers, artificial leather adhesives, coatings, etc. It prevents aging and improves color stability to prolong the service life of the products.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 81
data.description: Dragonsorb® 81 is a benzophenone-type UV absorber that is widely used in polyolefin and other polymers such as plasticized PVC and rubber products. It is mainly used in LDPE and LLDPE agricultural films, EVA copolymers, and HDPE injection products, such as turnover boxes, to slow down the degradation of products caused by exposure to sunlight. At the same time, it can be used as a UV shielding agent to protect the contents of industrial products and consumer packaging materials. In addition, it can have a synergistic effect with antioxidants and light stabilizers.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 111
data.description: Dragonsorb® 111 functions as a UV absorber. This slightly yellow solid is a blend of Dragonsorb® 119 and Dragonsorb® 622 which are light stabilizers compatible with polymers such as polyethylenes (PE), thermoplastic polyolefins (TPO), polypropylene (PP), acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS), etc.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 119
data.description: Dragonsorb® 119 is a polymer hindered amine light stabilizer (HALS), suitable for PE agricultural film, PP fiber and talc-filled PP, and TPO auto parts. This product can also be used in powder coating, which not only brings a triboelectric effect but also light stability. Generally, the addition level ranges between 0.05 and 1%.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 120
data.description: Dragonsorb® 120 is a sterically hindered hydroxybenzoate UV absorber, which converts UV radiation into heat energy through reversible chemical rearrangement. When compared to benzotriazole UV absorbers, it can provide excellent initial color and has a synergistic effect with hindered amine light stabilizer. It can be used with a hindered phenol antioxidant, a phosphite antioxidant, and a hindered amine light stabilizer at the same time to improve the weatherability of outdoor products. It can also be used simultaneously with benzotriazole UV absorbers to improve the weatherability of products, such as TPO car bumpers. The recommended use level of this product in PP, PE, TPO, PVC, EVA, unsaturated polyester, and ABS is 0.20 - 1.0%.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 123
data.description: Dragonsorb® 123 is a light stabilizer with low alkalinity. It is widely used in acrylic resin, polyurethane, sealant, adhesive, rubber, TPE and TPO blends, PVC, polystyrene, polypropylene, and other unsaturated resins. Additionally, as this product reacts in a cross-chain with other ingredients in the paint formula, it is especially recommended for the paint. It has excellent resistance to acid, flame retardant, sulfur, and catalyst residue.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 144
data.description: Dragonsorb® 144 is a light stabilizer of the hindered amine class (HALS). This product also contains an antioxidant moiety of the sterically hindered phenol type. Its efficiency provides a significantly extended lifetime to coatings by minimizing paint defects such as cracking and loss of gloss. It has a tribo-gun effect for powder coating to increase powder static adhesion.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 196
data.description: Dragonsorb® 196 is a highly efficient liquid-type UV absorber with an active UV absorbance wavelength in the range of 240 ~ 355 nm. Due to its excellent UV absorbing functionality, it can effectively restrain the yellowing of the material. This product is especially suitable for PU and epoxy materials.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 234
data.description: Dragonsorb® 234 is a highly effective UV absorber for polymers that are usually processed at high temperatures. These polymers include polycarbonate, polyesters, polyacetal, polyamides, polyphenylene sulfide, ABS compounding, polyphenylene oxide, aromatic copolymers, thermoplastic polyurethane, and polyurethane fibers.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 292
data.description: Dragonsorb® 292 is a hindered amine light stabilizer that is mainly used in paints, coatings, inks, polyurethane paints, etc. This product has a synergistic effect with ultraviolet absorbers. It can effectively prevent the coating from maintaining luster under sun exposure and avoid cracking, spots, and surface peeling, thus greatly improving the coating life. This effect is better in automobile coatings.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 312

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 2-Ethoxy-2′-ethyloxalic acid bisanilide, 2-Ethoxy-2′-ethyloxanilide, 2-Ethyl-2′-ethoxyoxalanilide, 2′-Ethoxy-2′′-ethyloxanilide, Chiguard 1033, Hostavin VSU, N 1-(2-Ethoxyphenyl)-N 2-(2-ethylphenyl)ethanediamide, N′-(2-Ethoxyphenyl)-N-(2-ethylphenyl)oxamide

data.description: Dragonsorb® 312 has a low-volatile polar substance and good thermal stability. Contact with metal ions will not decolorize, especially with short-wavelength ultraviolet light. Therefore, it is often used as a brightener and stabilizer of UV curing systems. This product is recommended for PA, PC, PVC, PU, and PET/PBT resins.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 320
data.description: Dragonsorb® 320 is a highly effective light stabilizer that features strong UV absorption, low volatility, and excellent compatibility with a variety of substrates. It protects polymers as well as organic pigments from UV radiation, which helps preserve the original appearance and physical integrity of molded articles, films, sheets, and fibers during outdoor weathering. This product is slightly more discoloring than conventional UV absorbers. It can be used for a variety of plastics and other organic substrates, including unsaturated polyesters, PVC, and PVC plastisol. Additionally, good results are expected when this product is used in polycarbonates, polyurethanes, polyamides, and synthetic fibers, particularly those with a polyester, epoxy, or isocyanate resin base.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 326
data.description: Dragonsorb® 326 is an important ultraviolet absorber of the benzotriazole series. This slightly yellow UV absorber is non-toxic and has good stability. It has higher absorbency for ultraviolet rays and is widely used for photosensitive materials, polymerized materials, coatings, and so on.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 327
data.description: Dragonsorb® 327 is a UV absorber that can strongly absorb 270 ~ 400nm ultraviolet light with low volatility and good chemical stability. The combination of the ultraviolet absorber 327 and an antioxidant has an obvious synergistic effect. This product has excellent heat resistance and washing resistance. It has good compatibility with polyolefin and is suitable for polyethylene, polypropylene, PVC, polymethylmethacrylate, polyformaldehyde, polyurethane, unsaturated polyester, ABS, epoxy resin, cellulose resin, etc. The recommended dosage level of this product in plastic is generally 0.3 - 0.5%.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 328
data.description: Dragonsorb® 328 is an excellent ultraviolet absorbent with a UVmax of 345nm. It has good polymer solubility and low volatility and is mainly used for PE, PP, PS, PVC, polyester, ABS, and so on. This pale yellowish powder has a melting point of 81°C and is soluble in benzene, toluene, ethyl acetate, and petroleum ether; slightly soluble in ethyl alcohol and methyl alcohol; and insoluble in water.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 329
data.description: Dragonsorb® 329 is an effective anti-aging agent with excellent performance. It is soluble in benzene, styrene, and ethyl acetate, slightly soluble in ethanol, and insoluble in water. This substance can absorb UV light of 270 - 340nm and is widely used in PE, PVC, PP, PS, PC, polypropylene fiber, ABS resin, epoxy resin, resin fiber, and vinyl acetate. It can also be used in plastic containers, food packaging boxes, and other packaging materials, providing them with a good light stability effect. The recommended dosage is 0.1% - 0.5%, and for thick products, it is 0.05 - 0.2%.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 360
data.description: Dragonsorb® 360 is a dimeric 2-hydroxy benzotriazole UV absorber used in a variety of polymers and resin compositions. This product has very low volatility and high thermostability. It can be used in polyacrylic resin, polyalkene, polyamide, and elastoplastic goods with good compatibility and higher UV absorbability. This yellowish powder is insoluble in water, and soluble in esters and benzoid solvents. It shows a synergistic effect when used with other additives such as antioxidants.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 571
data.description: Dragonsorb® 571 has good thermal stability and compatibility with various polymers. It can be widely used in thermoplastic PUR, coatings, and foam materials. It can also be used for rigid and plastic PVC, PVB, PMMA, PVDC, EVOH, EVA, heat-curing unsaturated resin and PA, PET and EVA rolls, and fiber. This product is also suitable for latex, wax, adhesives, homogeneous polystyrene and its copolymers, elastomers, and polyolefins.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 622

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 1-(2-Hydroxyethyl)-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-4-piperidinol-dimethyl succinate copolymer, 4-Hydroxy-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-1-piperidinethanol-dimethyl succinate copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-1-(2-hydroxyethyl)-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-4-piperidinol copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-1-(2-hydroxyethyl)-4-hydroxy-2,2,6,6-tetramethylpiperidine copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-2-(4-hydroxy-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-1-piperidyl)ethanol copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-4-hydroxy-1-(2-hydroxyethyl)-2,2,6,6-tetramethylpiperidine copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-4-hydroxy-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-1-piperidineethanol copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-4-hydroxy-2,2,6,6-tetramethyl-1-piperidylethanol copolymer, Dimethyl succinate-4-hydroxy-2,2,6,6,-tetramethyl-1-piperidineethanol

data.description: Dragonsorb® 622 is a hindered amine light stabilizer that can be used in polyethylene, polypropylene, polyurethane, POM, polyamide, and polyester elastomers. It can also be used in ABS and engineering plastics. This product is approved for food packaging in some countries.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 765
data.description: Dragonsorb® 765 is a UV absorber and light stabilizer that is mainly used for polyethylenes (PE), polypropylenes (PP), polyesters, and coatings.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 770
data.description: Dragonsorb® 770 is a hindered amine light stabilizer used for anti-photooxidation aging of polyethylene, polypropylene, and polystyrene products. It also has a good effect on ABS resin, polyurethane, polyester, and other plastics. This product provides good light stability on plastic moldings, even when used in small quantities. When working with antioxidants, it improves heat resistance, and when mixed with other UV absorbers, it provides greater UV resistance.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 783
data.description: Dragonsorb® 783 has good compatibility, processing thermal stability, oil resistance, water resistance, and extraction resistance. This product reflects the mechanisms of various light stabilizers and has the best synergistic and complementary effect. It can be used for food packaging and is mainly used for PE agricultural film, polyethylene, polypropylene, polyurethane, polyamide, and polyester elastomers. This product can also be used in ABS and engineering plastics.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 791
data.description: Dragonsorb® 791 is a synergistic mixture of oligomeric hindered amine light stabilizers (a mixture of light stabilizers 770 and 944). It is an excellent light stabilizer for thick products, such as car bumpers, dashboards, garden tables and chairs, etc. The synergistic effect between the high molecular weight and low molecular weight hindered amine light stabilizer components in Dragonsorb® 791 maximizes the protection of the polymer from degradation due to UV radiation and long-term heating. Its application fields include PP, PP/EPDM, and PP/PE/EPDM mixture (TPO class).

data.name: Dragonsorb® 928
data.description: Dragonsorb® 928 functions as a UV absorber. This product is compatible with polyamides.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 944
data.description: Dragonsorb® 944 imparts excellent light stability in polyolefins (PP, PE, and PVC), PA, polyacetals, and polyester. This product shows excellent compatibility and high resistance to extraction. When used with other HALS, it has an excellent synergistic effect. In addition, it can be used in food packaging materials. HALS944 is now one of the most advanced HALS that is widely used both at home and abroad.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 1084
data.description: Dragonsorb® 1084 is mainly used in polyethylene greenhouse films and agricultural films. It has strong compatibility with polyolefin products, and when used in polyethylene agricultural films and polypropylene artificial turfs, it has high stability. This product has high pesticide and acid resistance and is widely used in polypropylene, polyethylene fiber, artificial turf, and other fields. Additionally, it can be used with other forms of stabilizers, especially UV absorbers.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 1130
data.description: Dragonsorb® 1130 is a liquid UV absorber of the hydroxyphenylbenzotriazole class specifically developed for coatings. This product is miscible with all common solvents and can also be easily incorporated into water-borne systems. The high temperature and extraction resistance of Dragonsorb® 1130 makes it especially suitable for industrial and automotive coatings. Because of its broad UV absorption, this product also provides efficient protection to light-sensitive substrates such as wood and plastics.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 1164
data.description: Dragonsorb® 1164 is a highly effective UV absorber that is suitable for nylon and other engineering plastics.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 1577
data.description: Dragonsorb® 1577 is a UV absorber whose applications include polyalkene terephthalates and naphthalates, linear and branched polycarbonates, modified polyphenylene ether compounds, and various high-performance plastics. Relevant applications also include the use of homo-, co-, or terpolymer structural compositions in thermoplastic materials. The use of this product is indicated in polymer blends and alloys, such as PC/ABS, PC/PBT, PPE/IPS, PPE/PA, and copolymers, as well as in reinforced, filled, and/or flame-retardant compounds, which can be transparent, translucent, and/or pigmented. Due to its very low chelating tendency, formulations in polymers containing catalyst residues are possible.
